{
  "slug": "the-beekeeper-madame-web-and-a-dumpuary-extravaganza",
  "title": "‘The Beekeeper,’ ‘Madame Web,’ and a Dumpuary Extravaganza",
  "show": "The Big Picture",
  "network": "The Ringer",
  "hosts": [
    "Sean Fennessy",
    "Amanda Dobbins",
    "Chris Ryan"
  ],
  "published": "2024-02-16",
  "runtimeMin": 96,
  "format": "Three January dregs: Chris Ryan on the improbable hit ‘The Beekeeper,’ then Sean and Amanda on the wreck of ‘Madame Web’ and Jennifer Lopez's self-funded ‘This Is Me…Now.’",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘The Beekeeper’",
      "note": "with Chris Ryan",
      "guest": "Chris Ryan on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "The Beekeeper",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "David Ayer's Jason Statham revenge picture: a literal beekeeper turns out to be a deactivated black-ops agent and goes up the ladder of an elder-scam ring that runs to the White House. Chris reads it as a Death Wish for the age of phishing, part Q-shaman-as-assassin, part Taxi Driver, part Jan. 6, and calls it the biggest movie of 2024 so far."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "‘Madame Web’",
      "note": "15 questions",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Madame Web",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "S.J. Clarkson's Sony Spider-Man prequel about a paramedic (Dakota Johnson) who sees the future. Sean calls it one of the worst studio movies of the decade: Tahar Rahim's whole performance ADR'd, a 2003 setting that plays like 1994, a Toxic team-up teased and abandoned, and the meme trailer line cut from the film. Structured as 15 questions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "‘This Is Me…Now: A Love Story’",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "This Is Me...Now: A Love Story",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Jennifer Lopez's $20M self-funded musical visual album, now Amazon's: a mechanical heart fed flower petals, Fat Joe as her therapist, a Zodiac council (Post Malone is the Leo), and Ben Affleck under prosthetics as a cable-news anchor. Amanda had a good time; Sean compares the self-mythologizing to Billy Joel's Glass Houses."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Greatest Love Story Never Told",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "The making-of documentary, out Feb. 27 on Prime; Ben Affleck features. Amanda's looking forward to it."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
